H01/P01/1/The runes look like they might represent compass directions rather than letters.
H02/P01/2/Notice how some runes line up with the way the wind and waves move around the gate.
H03/P01/3/Try rotating the runes so they all point toward the same cardinal direction.

H04/P02/1/The sundial only tells time correctly when the gnomon is aligned with the light source.
H05/P02/2/Pay attention to the shadow at a specific time of day mentioned in any nearby notes or carvings.
H06/P02/3/Set the gnomon to the hour when the sun is highest in the sky here.

H07/P03/1/The door is called TideLock for a reason; think about high tide and low tide.
H08/P03/2/The markings near the edges look like a rising and falling water line.
H09/P03/3/Match the symbols to the water level at low tide to release the lock.

H10/P04/1/Each crystal hums at a slightly different pitch when you touch it.
H11/P04/2/Listen for a short melody or pattern that repeats when the crystals glow brightest.
H12/P04/3/Touch the crystals in the order of lowest pitch to highest pitch.

H13/P05/1/The stones respond to the direction and strength of the wind.
H14/P05/2/Try arranging the weights so the wind can pass smoothly through the circle instead of being blocked.
H15/P05/3/Place the heaviest weights where the wind is weakest and the lightest where it hits strongest.

H16/P06/1/The beacon will only work if every component is placed in the correct slot.
H17/P06/2/Look at the shapes and symbols next to each slot; they match marks on the components.
H18/P06/3/Match each component to the slot with the same symbol, then ignite the center to activate the beacon.